    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips and add to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Strip the<strong> rosemary leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems, then sprinkle the<strong> chopped rosemary </strong>all over the chips and put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until crisp \u2013 these are your <strong>rosemary chips</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-ultimate-veggie-cheeseburger-with-tomato-relish/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the<strong> tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> roughly</p><p>Heat a pot with 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped tomato</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until beginning to break down</p><p>Whilst the tomatoes are cooking, peel and finely chop (or grate) the<strong> garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-ultimate-veggie-cheeseburger-with-tomato-relish/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>tomato paste</strong> to the pot and cook for 30 secs further</p><p>Add 100ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [150ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> with the<strong> balsamic vinegar</strong> and 1 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span><strong> sugar</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for 5-6 min or until the tomatoes have broken down and the sauce is the consistency of ketchup \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato relish</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-ultimate-veggie-cheeseburger-with-tomato-relish/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Line a baking tray with<strong> baking paper</strong>, then add the <strong>meat-free burger patties</strong>\u00a0to one side and put in the oven for an initial 10 min</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-ultimate-veggie-cheeseburger-with-tomato-relish/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the chips and burgers are in the oven, wash the <strong>gem lettuce</strong>, then remove 4 <span class=\"text-danger\">[8]</span> <strong>outer leaves </strong>and chop the inner core<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> into quarters</p><p>Peel and slice the<strong> shallot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into rounds</p><p>Grate the <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-ultimate-veggie-cheeseburger-with-tomato-relish/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the patties have had 10 min, remove the tray from the oven and top them with the <strong>grated cheese</strong> \u2013 these are your <strong>cheesy patties</strong></p><p>Slice the <strong>brioche</strong> <strong>buns</strong> in half</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-ultimate-veggie-cheeseburger-with-tomato-relish/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>brioche halves</strong> to the other side of the tray (cooking for 4? You may need two trays!)</p><p>Return the tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> to the oven for 2-3 min or until the cheese has melted and the brioche has warmed through</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-ultimate-veggie-cheeseburger-with-tomato-relish/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Spread the <strong>warmed brioche halves</strong> with a dollop of <strong>tomato relish</strong>, then layer up the <strong>lettuce leaves</strong>, <strong>cheesy patties</strong> and <strong>sliced shallot </strong>\u2013 these are your<strong> ultimate veggie cheeseburgers</strong></p><p>Serve the<strong> rosemary chips</strong> and <strong>lettuce quarters</strong> to the side with any <strong>remaining tomato relish</strong> for dipping</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
